A police duct tape at the bus stop near University of South Africa (Unisa) campus where another body of a homeless man was discovered with stab wounds June 19, 2019 in Pretoria, South Africa. JOHANNESBURG - Two homeless people believed to have been killed by the so-called Capital Killer have finally been laid to rest. This almost two months after their bodies were discovered in Muckleneuk, Pretoria. READ: Suspect not linked to capital killings: NPA Altogether five homeless men were either stabbed or bludgeoned to death. Their bodies were found in different parts of the suburb in June. Police say they will not be disclosing the men's identities because the matter is still under investigation.